24 years since the death of Hu Yaobang
2013-04-15 07:22:16 GMT
By Jia Xiaoguang, Sina EnglishApril 15th, 2013 marks the 24th anniversary of the death of Hu Yaobang, who served as the General Secretary of Chinese Communist Party (CCP) from 1982 to 1987.Liberation Daily, one of China’s most influential official newspapers, published a commemorative article today which hails Hu’s spearheading role in pushing forward China’s opening, reform and modernization process.“We remember Hu Yaobang as a man who is kind, honest, selfless and magnanimous, a leader who is bent on innovation and undaunted by the headwind against reform.” the article comments.
